Based on the properties of non-archimedean local fields, the valuation is uniquely determined by the ring of integers (the maximal compact subring), which is preserved by any continuous ring automorphism (and all ring automorphisms of local fields are continuous).

```lean
lemma valuation_ringEquiv {L : Type*} [Field L] [ValuativeRel L] [TopologicalSpace L]
    [IsNonarchimedeanLocalField L] (e : L ≃+* L) (x : L) :
    valuation L (e x) = valuation L x :=
  Valuation.ext fun y => by
    rw [← mem_ringOfIntegers, ← mem_ringOfIntegers, ← ringOfIntegers.map_eq e]
    simp
```
